Health Minister Zweli Mkhize has briefed the National Council of Provinces on the country's vaccine rollout strategy on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says the second phase of the vaccine rollout could take up to six months. Mkhize updated the National Council of Provinces on the vaccine rollout in South Africa. READ: Over 32,000 healthcare workers vaccinated: Mkhize The minister says it will include frontline workers and people with co-morbidities. 